input: 3 1 2 2 1 2 3 3 
k=2 

check the element occurs mor then n/k times where n is length of array 

output: 2 

logic:
  1. iterate array and get the count of each element exits
  2. convert int to Integer using boxed and in counting use summingInt for Integer
  3. itearte the map keyset with stream and filter if count i greater than n/k times and count it
  4. convert the result into (int)



import java.util.*;
import java.util.stream.*;
class Solution {
    // Function to find all elements in array that appear more than n/k times.
    public int countOccurence(int[] arr, int k) {
        // your code here,return the answer
        int nk= arr.length/k;
     Map<Integer,Integer> map  = Arrays.stream(arr).boxed().
        collect(Collectors.groupingBy(x->x , Collectors.summingInt(x->1)));
        
        return (int) map.entrySet().stream().filter(e -> e.getValue() >nk).count();
    }
}
